headline: Elevance reports lower-than-expected medical costs, confirms profit beat
summary: Elevance also reiterated its full-year profit forecast of $34.15 to $34.85 per share, and confirmed first-quarter adjusted shareholders' net income of $11.97 per share on Tuesday.  Analysts had expected a quarterly profit of $11.38 per share.  The company had come out with preliminary earnings numbers last week, amid a sharp stock selloff in the sector after UnitedHealth, which runs the country's largest health insurer, missed quarterly profit estimates due to elevated patient care costs in its Medicare Advantage business.

headline: Elevance brushes off fears of spiking Medicare Advantage costs
summary: Investors balked last week after UnitedHealth reported first-quarter MA utilization grew at twice its expected rate. Yet Elevance said spending was in line with expectations, a development one analyst called surprising.
